Package C2G8_Project

Class SchedulerStateTest

java.lang.Object
C2G8_Project.SchedulerStateTest
class SchedulerStateTest extends Object
Author:
Jordan JUnit5 Test Cases for SchedulerState.java (The Scheduler State Machine States) Overview: These test cases are intended to test the general functionality of the state machine (can states be set, changed, and can they all run their intended action based off of one method/command), as well as the logic of the specific state classes implemented for the scheduler to use (located in SchedulerStates.java). Example classes are used for the general functionality of the state machine, while the actual implemented classes are used for the logic testing. NOTE: The naming convention for each test is as follows: "State(s)_Test". Where is the state class (or groups of classes in the case of Example States), and is what the method does. For example, all example states used to test the functionality of the state machine start with "exampleStates_...", while actual implemented states in the scheduler (such as "Listening", "SendMessage", "PrepareFloorMessage", etc.) start with their name ("listeningState_...", "sendMessageState_...", and "prepareFloorMessageState_...", respectively). Anything that doesn't follow that naming convention is a test that follows the flow of these States in the scheduler system.
